# Standing Kelly execution authorization (Calendar Completion)

```text
ADR:           ADR-094
Effective:     2026-07-22
Applies when:  Kelly supplies or approves a Calendar Completion build script
```

## Rule

When an approved build script for CC-07…CC-12 (or the usability/AI-quality gate) is in the active user message, execute the **full ship cycle** without asking for routine confirmation to run, commit, push, or deploy.

## Ship cycle

Inspect → plan → edit in-scope → forward-only migrations → validators/tests/typecheck/build/lint/scans → repair defects → commit → push `main` → Netlify prod deploy → monitor → correct → redeploy → verify live routes → record evidence.

## Do not stop for

Routine difficulty, test failures, build failures, deploy failures, or correctable defects — diagnose, repair, revalidate, continue.

## Hard stops (hand off)

Destructive prod-data ops not in script · missing credentials · purchase/contract · material scope expansion · unrecoverable merge/data conflict · privacy/consent/legal/security decision not governed · production-data damage risk · unresolved platform permission barrier.

## Phase Two

ADR-093: no IC-01…IC-12 product implementation before CC-12. Extension points only during CC-07…CC-12.

## Synthesis

Do not mark Operator Usability Synthesis complete.

## Per-deliverable

One script = one deliverable. Do not absorb CC-08 while implementing CC-07.
